WRITE EXACTLY THREE PARAGRAPHS. STOP WHEN YOU REACH 1200 CHARACTERS.

END WITH A COMPLETE SENTENCE AND A PERIOD (.)

DO NOT STOP WRITING UNTIL YOU REACH AT LEAST 1000 CHARACTERS. THIS IS MANDATORY.

Your response must be substantive and detailed. DO NOT write short summaries.

In the 1980s, the Internet Protocol (IP) was developed, allowing different networks to communicate with each other.  The World Wide Web was invented in 1989 by Tim Berners-Lee, making it easier for people to access and share information using web browsers and hyperlinks. The internet expanded rapidly in the 1990s, with the widespread adoption of dial-up internet and the emergence of online services like America Online and CompuServe. As broadband internet became more prevalent, online activities like streaming and social media became possible.
